Class CodecToReplace

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rbbn.cpaas.mobile.utilities.CodecToReplace

  • public class CodecToReplace
extends java.lang.Object
    Model class to set the custom payload numbers to given codecs in SDP.

    1.4.0

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static CodecToReplace create(java.lang.String codecDefinition,
                                    java.lang.String payloadNumber,
                                    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> customProperties)
                             throws MobileException
        Factory method to create CodecToReplace instance.
        Parameters:
        codecDefinition - the codec that will be changed
        payloadNumber - new payload number that will be assigned to the codec, as described in RFC5761 this should be chosen from the range 96-127
        customProperties - properties of the codec that should be matched to original codec in order SDK to make the replace
        Throws:
        MobileException - when the payload number does not correspond to an integer value or not set in the range 96-127
        Since:
        1.4.0
